

Static Keyword

- it is used for memory management mainly
- it can used with
    - variables
    - methods
    - blocks
    - nested classes

- it belongs to the class than an instance of it

    1. Static Variable
         - it can be used to refer to the common property of all objects
         - it gets memory only once in the class area at the time of class loading

         advantages -> makes your program memory efficient

    2. Static method
        - it belongs to class rather than instance of a class
        - it can be invoked without creating an object of that class
        - it can access the static data member and can modify its value

        restrictions on static method
            - it cannot use non-static data member or call non-static method directly
            - this and super cannot be used in static context


    3. Static block
        - it is used to initialize static data member
        - it is executed before the main method at the time of class loading

